        "# Download the README we created (or copy from Claude output)\n",
        "%%writefile /content/vscode_agent_app/README.md\n",
        "\n",
        "# 🤖 VS Code Docs AI Agent\n",
        "\n",
        "An AI-powered documentation assistant that answers questions about Visual Studio Code by searching through the official VS Code documentation. Built as part of the [AI Agents Crash Course](https://alexeygrigorev.com/aihero/) by Alexey Grigorev.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "**Problem:** VS Code has hundreds of documentation pages. Finding the right answer to a specific question means manually searching through dozens of files.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Solution:** This AI agent automatically searches through 5,700+ indexed documentation sections and provides accurate, source-cited answers in seconds.\n",
        "\n",
        "**How it works:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Downloads and parses all markdown files from the [microsoft/vscode-docs](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs) GitHub repository\n",
        "2. Splits documents into semantic sections (by `##` headers) for precise retrieval\n",
        "3. Indexes sections using TF-IDF text search\n",
        "4. When a user asks a question, searches the index and sends relevant sections to an LLM\n",
        "5. The LLM generates a grounded answer based only on the search results\n",
        "\n",
        "## Features\n",
        "\n",
        "- **RAG Pipeline** — Retrieval-Augmented Generation using indexed VS Code documentation\n",
        "- **Section-Based Chunking** — Splits docs by markdown headers for semantically complete chunks\n",
        "- **Text Search** — TF-IDF keyword matching via minsearch\n",
        "- **Grounded Answers** — LLM responds only from search results, cites sources\n",
        "- **Out-of-Scope Detection** — Correctly declines questions outside VS Code docs\n",
        "- **Chat Interface** — Streamlit web UI with conversation history\n",
        "- **Interaction Logging** — All conversations saved as JSON for evaluation\n",
        "- **LLM-as-a-Judge Evaluation** — Automated quality checks on agent responses\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tech Stack\n",
        "\n",
        "| Component | Technology |\n",
        "|-----------|-----------|\n",
        "| LLM | Groq (Llama 3.3 70B, free tier) |\n",
        "| Framework | Pydantic AI |\n",
        "| Search | minsearch (TF-IDF + cosine similarity) |\n",
        "| Embeddings | sentence-transformers |\n",
        "| UI | Streamlit |\n",
        "| Data Source | microsoft/vscode-docs GitHub repo |\n",
        "| Runtime | Google Colab |\n",
        "\n",
        "## Installation\n",
        "\n",
        "### Prerequisites\n",
        "\n",
        "- Python 3.10+\n",
        "- A free [Groq API key](https://console.groq.com)\n",
        "\n",
        "### Setup\n",
        "```bash\n",
        "git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/vscode-docs-agent.git\n",
        "cd vscode-docs-agent\n",
        "pip install -r requirements.txt\n",
        "export GROQ_API_KEY=\"gsk_your_key_here\"\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### Running the App\n",
        "```bash\n",
        "streamlit run app.py\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "## Evaluation\n",
        "\n",
        "Evaluated using **LLM-as-a-Judge** — a separate LLM grades each response against quality criteria.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Results: Agent v1 vs v2\n",
        "\n",
        "| Metric | Agent v1 | Agent v2 |\n",
        "|--------|----------|----------|\n",
        "| instructions_follow | 33% | **78%** |\n",
        "| answer_relevant | 58% | **89%** |\n",
        "| tool_call_search | 67% | **78%** |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key finding:** Improving the system prompt increased answer relevance by **31 percentage points**.\n",
        "\n",
        "- 23 interaction logs collected\n",
        "- 21 evaluations completed\n",
        "- 10 AI-generated test questions\n",
        "\n",
        "## What I Learned\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Data preparation is 50% of the work** — Days 1-3 were all about data before touching AI\n",
        "2. **Chunking strategy matters** — Section-based beats sliding window for structured markdown\n",
        "3. **Open-source LLMs have tool-calling limitations** — Direct RAG injection is more reliable\n",
        "4. **System prompts are measurable** — Evaluation metrics proved prompt changes have quantifiable impact\n",
        "5. **Free-tier APIs are sufficient for learning** — Entire project built on Groq free tier\n",
